</div>
</div>



<p>We also verified that SSH host keys persist across task restarts — the server fingerprint stays the same after a forced redeployment, thanks to the EFS volume mounted at <code>/etc/ssh/</code>.</p>

<h2>
  <a name="conclusion" href="#conclusion">
  </a>
  Conclusion
</h2>

<p>S3 Files bridges the gap between file system and object storage in a way that makes a lot of expensive AWS services feel redundant. For SFTP specifically, the combination of atmoz/sftp + S3 Files on Fargate gives you:</p>

<ul>
<li>
<strong>~8x lower cost</strong> than Transfer Family</li>
<li>
<strong>Full control</strong> over the SFTP server</li>
<li>
<strong>Native S3 event notifications</strong> for event-driven processing</li>
<li>
<strong>S3 as the source of truth</strong> — lifecycle rules, replication, analytics all work</li>
<li>
<strong>Infrastructure as Code</strong> with Terraform (even before native provider support)</li>
</ul>

<p>The days of paying $216/month minimum for a managed SFTP endpoint are over for most teams. S3 Files is the missing piece that makes DIY SFTP on AWS not just viable, but ~8x cheaper.</p>


